# Gutenberg Block Standards

## Scaffolding and layout

Scaffold with: `npx @wordpress/create-block@latest --no-plugin --variant=dynamic my-block`

Inside an existing plugin:
```
my-plugin/
├── src/blocks/<block-name>/
│   ├── block.json       # apiVersion: 3
│   ├── index.js         # registerBlockType entry
│   ├── edit.js          # editor UI
│   ├── save.js          # static save (or omit for dynamic)
│   ├── render.php       # dynamic render (if dynamic)
│   ├── view.js          # frontend-only JS
│   ├── editor.scss      # editor-only styles
│   └── style.scss       # shared styles
└── build/               # generated, gitignored
```

Register from `build/`, never from `src/`.

## block.json — canonical example

```json
{
  "$schema": "https://schemas.wp.org/trunk/block.json",
  "apiVersion": 3,
  "name": "my-plugin/featured-product",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "title": "Featured Product",
  "category": "widgets",
  "textdomain": "my-plugin",
  "supports": {
    "html": false,
    "align": ["wide", "full"],
    "spacing": { "padding": true, "margin": true },
    "color": { "background": true, "text": true }
  },
  "attributes": {
    "productId": { "type": "integer", "default": 0 },
    "showPrice": { "type": "boolean", "default": true },
    "headline":  { "type": "string", "source": "html", "selector": "h2" }
  },
  "editorScript": "file:./index.js",
  "editorStyle":  "file:./editor.css",
  "style":        "file:./style.css",
  "viewScriptModule": "file:./view.js",
  "render":       "file:./render.php"
}
```

Rules:
- `apiVersion: 3` always (WP 6.9+ enforces it; older breaks iframed editor style isolation)
- `textdomain` must match PHP plugin slug exactly
- Every attribute declared with `type`. Sourced attrs also get `source` + `selector`
- Don't store transient UI state as block attributes — use React state
- `viewScriptModule` (preferred over `viewScript`) for modern ES module frontend JS
- Anything not in block.json won't load inside the iframed editor

## PHP registration

```php
add_action( 'init', static function () {
    register_block_type( __DIR__ . '/build/blocks/featured-product' );
} );
// For many blocks:
foreach ( glob( __DIR__ . '/build/blocks/*/block.json' ) as $json ) {
    register_block_type( dirname( $json ) );
}
```

Do NOT also call `wp_enqueue_script` for the same handles — it's redundant.

## edit.js pattern

```jsx
import { __ } from '@wordpress/i18n';
import { useBlockProps, InspectorControls, RichText } from '@wordpress/block-editor';
import { PanelBody, ToggleControl } from '@wordpress/components';

export default function Edit( { attributes, setAttributes } ) {
    const { headline, showPrice } = attributes;
    return (
        <>
            <InspectorControls>
                <PanelBody title={ __( 'Display', 'my-plugin' ) }>
                    <ToggleControl
                        label={ __( 'Show price', 'my-plugin' ) }
                        checked={ showPrice }
                        onChange={ ( v ) => setAttributes( { showPrice: v } ) }
                    />
                </PanelBody>
            </InspectorControls>
            <div { ...useBlockProps() }>
                <RichText tagName="h2" value={ headline }
                    onChange={ ( v ) => setAttributes( { headline: v } ) }
                    placeholder={ __( 'Add a headline…', 'my-plugin' ) } />
            </div>
        </>
    );
}
```

Hard rules:
- Always spread `useBlockProps()` on the wrapper — alignment, color, spacing styles depend on it
- `InspectorControls` for sidebar settings, never custom sidebar
- `RichText` for editable text, never raw `contenteditable`
- `MediaUpload` / `MediaUploadCheck` from `@wordpress/block-editor` for media

## Dynamic vs static

**Dynamic (server-rendered):**
- `save()` returns `null`
- `render.php` uses `$attributes`, `$content`, `$block`; echoes `get_block_wrapper_attributes()` on wrapper
- Escape everything in render.php: `esc_html()`, `esc_attr()`, `wp_kses_post()`
- Prefer dynamic blocks — no migration tax when markup changes

**Static (HTML stored in post):**
- `save()` returns real JSX markup
- No `render` in block.json
- Changing markup later requires a `deprecated` migration or users see "Invalid block"
- Only use when server rendering isn't needed

## Common block pitfalls

| Symptom | Cause |
|---|---|
| Editor styles not loading | File not listed in block.json (`editorStyle`/`style`) |
| "Invalid block" after save | `save()` markup changed; write a `deprecated` entry |
| Attribute resets on reload | Reading React state but never calling `setAttributes` |
| Block works in editor not FE | Dynamic blocks need `render`, not just `save` |
| `useBlockProps` missing | No alignment/classes/styles applied |
| `script` vs `viewScript` | `script` loads BOTH editor + FE; `viewScriptModule` is FE-only |
